# 1. Project Identity & Strategic Context

**Freshness: High - verified in the Phase 3 completion session.**

EvalForge is the portfolio-grade LLM evaluation product at
`/Users/fortunevieyra/Documents/Github/ai-projects/llm-evaluation-dashboard`. It uses FastAPI,
Streamlit, SQLAlchemy/Alembic, SQLite or PostgreSQL, and custom deterministic metrics. Its product
goal is to let a reviewer compare prompt/model candidates on shared test cases, inspect case-level
evidence, understand hallucination/relevance/correctness-style scores, and export a trustworthy
record without presenting an AI-demo interface.

Phase 2 established the restrained work-app UI. Phase 3 added the identity, tenant, execution,
provider-safety, export, PostgreSQL, container, and release-proof foundations most likely needed for
shared use. Zero-cost local demo mode remains the default. Shared/public, paid-provider, and hosted
claims remain separate authority and proof layers.

